NEW MODULE_DOMAIN_DESCRIPTION constant value:
"""The RMS (Resource Management System) module handles task assignments
and timesheet logging for a software/engineering company.

Available collections:
- rms_timesheet: PRIMARY collection. Used for viewing assigned tasks,
  filling/logging worklog hours, and approving submitted worklogs.
  This is where day-to-day work tracking happens.
- rms_projectplan: Project Manager workflows ONLY. Used for creating
  formal project plans, scheduling phases, defining project structure.
  Currently NOT implemented in our system. Only route here if the
  message explicitly uses project-planning language like "create
  project plan", "set up project schedule", "define project phases".

Available personas:
- CREATOR: Creates new task assignments. Example actions: assigning a
  task to themselves or to a reportee with project ID, product ID,
  task index, planned hours, and date range.
- REVIEWER (also called FILLER): Views their assigned tasks and logs
  hours worked against them. They do NOT create tasks. Their default
  action when they say "show tasks" is to see what's assigned so they
  can fill hours. Logging hours / filling timesheets is ALWAYS the
  REVIEWER persona.
- APPROVER: Reviews completed worklogs from team members and approves
  or rejects them. Senior team leads have this role for their reportees.

CRITICAL DISAMBIGUATION RULES:
1. "log hours", "fill hours", "fill timesheet", "log 8 hours today",
   "log time on task X" -> ALWAYS REVIEWER + rms_timesheet, NEVER
   CREATOR. Logging hours is not the same as creating a task.
2. "show my tasks", "what tasks do I have", "list my assignments",
   "my pending entries", "what's on my plate today" -> REVIEWER +
   rms_timesheet (viewing assignments to fill hours against).
3. "create task", "assign task to <person>", "set up a new task for
   me on project X" -> CREATOR + rms_timesheet (default — unless
   message specifically uses project-planning language).
4. "approve worklog 5", "reject worklog 3", "show pending approvals",
   "approve all" -> APPROVER + rms_timesheet.
5. "create project plan", "set up project schedule for project X",
   "define project phases" -> CREATOR + rms_projectplan (rare).
6. Anything not related to tasks, timesheets, projects, or worklogs ->
   OUT_OF_DOMAIN. This includes weather, jokes, general questions,
   personal queries, other modules' topics."""

